      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"1. LET'S GO SPIKE produced a modest effort most recently when eighth at Cannington over 275m behind South Crenshaw (16.64) in a Grade 6. Won at his only start from this box. Key runner on his best form. 8. NITRO'S RUBY flew the lids from the middle with a slick turn of foot and stuck on well despite missing the frame, finishing sixth over 300m Mandurah in 17.72. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. 3. SURELY beaten last start over the 297m at this track but finished in the minors in a speedy 17.28. Harder here but expected to measure up. 2. RUN DON'T WALK can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.\",\"runners\":[1,8,3,2],\"exclusive\":false}",
